    <div class="panel fbla-work">
      <div class="panel-title">
        <h1>FBLA Chapter Haiti</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="content">
        <div class="logo">
          <%= image_tag 'FBLA-logo.png' %>
        </div>

        <div class="description">
          <p>
            <b>Future Business Leaders of America-Phi Beta Lambda, Inc. (FBLA-PBL)</b>
            is the largest career student business organization in the world.
            Each year, FBLA-PBL helps over 230,000 members prepare for careers
            in business.<br><br>

            For the past 10 years, we have been the sole school representing the
            country of Haiti. All necessary US visas, hotel
            reservations, and airfare are secured on the behalf our participants.<br><br>

            This is far beyond a simple trip abroad or tourism, the impact on our
            students leaves a lasting mark on their work ethics, career outlooks,
            and ambitions.<br><br>

            Our students participate in competitive business-related events and come
            away with a stronger sense of the skills necessary to succeed in modern
            business.<br><br>

            In 20 years of educating in the NYC public schools, instituting
            FBLA in many high schools, I've seen first-hand the impact of
            the program on building cross-cultural experience, networking,
            internships, volunteering, student performance, self-reliance,
            passion projects and collegiate preparation.<br><br>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel icdh">
      <div class="panel-title">
        <h1>ICDH</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="content">
        <div class="logo">
          <%= image_tag 'icdh-logo.png' %>
        </div>

        <div class="description">
          <p>
            <b>Institution Chrétienne d'Haïti</b> is a K-12 school located in Carrefour
            since 2000. Our curriculum offers musical arts, science and math. Our
            languages courses span from Haitian Creole, French, English, Spanish,
            and Mandarin Chinese.<br><br>

            In 2011, our school boasted a 100% percentage of success
            in Haitian state examinations at all levels. That level of excellence
            persists, as we wish to excel on an international scale.<br><br>

            Our school acts as a pillar in our community and commonly participates
            in scholastic events with neighboring schools and colleges.<br><br>

            Beyond K-12, our continuing education programs for learning languages
            and professional development are highly lauded. While we often train
            our own staff, the program is freely available to professionals from
            other schools. Raising the bar for education in Haiti is our goal,
            to that end we share our knowledge and expertise to all educators we can.<br><br>

            The American public schools are supported by local, state,
            federal governments and businesses. In Haiti, our establishment is
            supported solely by our non-profit organization.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
